ds - deadsearch
===============
deadsearch is a minimalistic and user-friendly menu utility designed for Linux systems. 

Installation
============
Clone the repository 

Create a build directory inside the project's folder

Change directory (cd) into the build folder 

Prepare makefiles for building with 

    cmake ..

Finally, build the software 

    make

Running ds 
==========
The program accepts input options from stdin by default. The chosen option will be sent to the program's stdout 

    echo "one two three" | ds 

More information and extendibility can be found inside the program's help page (-h flag)
